_Communications_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Presidential Communications Office\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidential_Communications_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Presidential_Communications_Group\"}, {\"begin\": 303, \"end\": 314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.015992884189637e-14, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yulo, 24, got rewarded P20 million from the Office of the President as he and the Philippines' delegation to the Paris Olympics paid Ferdinand \\\"Bongbong\\\" Marcos Jr. a courtesy call at the Malaca\\u00f1ang on Tuesday, August 13.\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 516, \"end\": 527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.015992884189637e-14, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}, {\"begin\": 567, \"end\": 576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ferdinand_VII_of_Spain\", \"score\": 0.9977490189277469, \"rank\": 0.0016941740265351678, \"text\": \"Ferdinand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ferdinand_VII_of_Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ferdinand_VII_of_Spain\"}, {\"begin\": 588, \"end\": 598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bongbong_Marcos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marcos Jr.\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bongbong_Marcos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bongbong_Marcos\"}, {\"begin\": 622, \"end\": 632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Office_of_the_President_of_the_Philippines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.874768050857265e-26, \"text\": \"Malaca\\u00f1ang\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Office_of_the_President_of_the_Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Office_of_the_President_of_the_Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is on top of theincentivesYulo, who also accepted the Presidential Medal of Merit, is entitled to get under Republic Act 10699 as he stands to pocket P10 million for each of his two gold medals.\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Boxing bronze medalistsAira VillegasandNesthy Petecio, meanwhile, scored P2 million apiece from the Office of the President in addition to the P2 million incentive they will each earn under the law.\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 1056, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yulo, Villegas, and Petecio were also granted an amity card from the Movie and Television Review and Classification Board valid until June 2025 and travel tax exemption valid until June 2028.\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Office of the President gave the rest of the 22-strongTeam PhilippinesP1 million apiece, with their coaches each getting P500,000.\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1385, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I thought what we should do is really recognize all the athletes.\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1453, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For an athlete - be it from the Philippines or wherever - to qualify for the Olympics is not an easy feat,\\\" said Marcos in a mix of Filipino and English.\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1486, \"end\": 1497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.015992884189637e-14, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That is an extremely difficult achievement to have managed.\\\"\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1670, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Marcos acknowledged that the rewards are not enough to compensate for the hardships the Philippines' latest set of Olympians have undergone.\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1760, \"end\": 1771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.015992884189637e-14, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I apologize if it is just a small amount.\", \"from\": 1814, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I know that P1 million is small if you compare it to your sacrifice and the experiences you went through.\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1962, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But for now, this is what we will do,\\\" said Marcos.\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 2014, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Celebrating its100th yearof Olympic participation, the Philippines enjoyed itsall-time best campaignas it won multiple gold medals in a single edition for the first time and matched its biggest medal haul in history.\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2071, \"end\": 2082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.015992884189637e-14, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Philippines finished tied with Hong Kong for 37th place in themedal tallyfor its highest Olympic ranking since 1964 and emerged as thebest performing Southeast Asian nation.\", \"from\": 2234, \"to\": 2411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2238, \"end\": 2249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.015992884189637e-14, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}, {\"begin\": 2269, \"end\": 2278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"score\": 0.9890198887165969, \"rank\": 0.009244022627500556, \"text\": \"Hong Kong\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\"}, {\"begin\": 2388, \"end\": 2403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southeast_Asia\", \"score\": 0.9999998178609696, \"rank\": 1.2678197933083758e-07, \"text\": \"Southeast Asian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southeast_Asia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southeast_Asia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marcos said he wants to aid the development of Philippine sports.\", \"from\": 2413, \"to\": 2478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If you can consider that all of these athletes who have done so well and have made us so proud, there is no official technical support from the government.\", \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2636, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They did it on their own,\\\" said Marcos.\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2676, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Of course they get help.\", \"from\": 2678, \"to\": 2703, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes, the government helps, but there is no formal structure to help our athletes and that is what we are going to establish now.\\\"\", \"from\": 2704, \"to\": 2839, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I ask all of you to tell us what is it that you need.\", \"from\": 2841, \"to\": 2895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"- Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2939, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"follow us\", \"from\": 2941, \"to\": 2950, \"entities\": []}]}"